# 6. 緊急企画、モモジャンカフェ！

Airi: Hello!
Haruka: Welcome to carino/carina!
Customers: I can't really see because of the curtains, but it definitely sounds like Airi Momoi and Haruka Kiritani are doing a shoot!
Customers: Yeah, I just saw in the news that they're both in a different idol group now. Do you think they're all here today?
Customers: Oh, what if this means they're gonna serve us...?! How amazing would that be?!
Airi: (Hehe. The customers sure all sound excited.)
Customers: Wait, where's Shizuku Hinomori...? I became a huge fan after seeing a recording of one of the shows she was on. I really wanted to see her in person...
Airi: Just a second. Shizuku's getting ready as we speak.
Customers: ...! Airi Momoi...!
Customers: Wait, getting ready? For...?
???: Welcome, everyone.
Shizuku: It's so wonderful to be making your acquaintance today. I hope you enjoy everything.
Customers: Sh...
Customers: She's looks so cool!!!
Staff: Wow...
Show Director: You, focus on Hinomori! Lock your camera onto her!
Haruka: So much excitement...
Airi: Her aura really is brilliant. Like, blindingly brilliant...
Haruka: Still, this was a great idea. How do you think they arrived on getting Shizuku to wear the male staff's uniform?
Airi: I guess it wouldn't have been all that interesting if we all just dressed as regular waitresses.
Airi: I thought we could do just that, but the stylist insisted she do this...
Haruka: Hehe. I see. And she looks stunning. I'm sure the customers are going to really enjoy this.
Customer: U-Um... Excuse me... Would you mind if we took a picture together?
Airi: Yes, of course!
Airi: Speaking of which, there's a nice area for taking pictures at the back of this cafe...
Airi: Why don't we go there? You may or may not appear on TV if that's okay.
Customer: Y-Yes, of course...! I don't mind as long I'm allowed to have a picture!
Airi: Great. Then, I'll go grab Shizuku now, so—
Customer: Oh...! N-No, I meant...
Airi: Huh?
Customer: I want to take a picture with you, Airi. I've been a fan of yours since you were still in training... And I watch MORE MORE JUMP! streams all the time.
Customer: You don't get many chances in life like this...! But I also apologize if I'm asking for too much...!
Airi: No, of course! Thank you for being such a fervent supporter.
Airi: Let's celebrate this moment by putting on the biggest smiles we can!
Customer: *Gasp* Airi...! She's right next to me...!
Haruka: Then, why don't I take it for you? Mind giving me your phone?
Customer: K-Kiritani?! You're taking it for us...?! Thank you so much! I don't know what to say...!
Haruka: Okay, smile.
Customer: Th-Thank you very much! I'll treasure this moment forever...!
Airi: Hehe. Promise? No hopping onto someone else's bandwagon, okay?
Airi: I won't forget what you told me today, and I look forward to seeing you at our next show.
Fujin: Whoa, hold up. We're allowed to ask for pictures? Take some with us next.
Wrestlers: Yeah, I wanna post them on PicShare! Let's take some as a group!
Haruka: Hehe. It's turned into a photo shoot all of a sudden.
Airi: Yeah. But I don't mind as long as we can use this area. Here, we should be able to stay out of the cafe staff's way.
Airi: Also... I appreciate that you want to post them on PicShare, but please make sure to mention this cafe and TV program when you do!
Minori: Hehe. Everyone's having so much fun!
Mizuki: Yeah, they're so caught up in trying to take pictures that we've been getting less orders!
Mizuki: This is our chance to get everything out!
Saki: Yeah, we can't let Airi's efforts go to waste!
Mizuki: Right! Also, Minori, thanks for jumping in to help with the kitchen! We feel so much better having you around.
Minori: No, I should be the one thanking you! Our shoot's been going well because you've all been doing such a great job so far!
Minori: Especially you, Mizuki. It's hard to believe this is your first day considering how many orders you've been handling!
Mizuki: If I'm gonna be honest, I was really worried in the beginning... But that massive pile of orders ended up being a good crash course.
Saki: Then, Mizuki, I've got a job for you! I just finished working on the bottom halves of these parfaits, so mind doing the whipped cream for me?
Mizuki: Yeah, you got it! These going to Emu's table, right?
Saki: Yup! And can you take these out to them when you're done?
Saki: After that, I'll need you to help decorate the waffles. But they still need some time to cook.
Mizuki: Okay!
Mizuki: Alright, I'm gonna make these look perfect!
Emu: Hehe... Everyone's having so much fun☆
Emu: Look at how their eyes are sparkling! It's like we're all a part of a big show!
Hinata: Hehe. You're right. And I'm looking forward to our parfaits.
Mizuki: Thank you very much for waiting! Here are your Mount Everest strawberry parfaits!
Emu: Oh, yay! Our Mount Everests have arrived♪
Hinata: Wow, they're so big...!
Mizuki: I'm sorry that they took a little longer than expected to make. Things have been so busy today that, well... I hope it hasn't been too much of a bother.
Emu: No, we've been having a lot of fun! We were just talking about how this all feels like a big show!
Mizuki: I'm glad you're both enjoying things so much! And I really hope you enjoy these!
Hinata: Actually, I'm surprised at how cute these parfaits are. I can see why so many people would want to take pictures and show their friends.
Emu: Yeah! I wanna take some for Nene and the others!
Emu: I mean, just look at this bow! It looks so real! It's a shame that we have to eat it!
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: Actually, I was the one who did all the whipped cream decorations for these...
Emu: What?! Mizuki, you made these?!
Hinata: But you said it's your first day here, no? You're so talented.
Mizuki: No, I'm just sorta good at decorating things. Still...
Mizuki: I really appreciate what you just said since I put everything I had into these.
Mizuki: And I guarantee that they taste amazing, so I really hope you enjoy them.
Emu: Yeah, then...
Emu: We promise to savor every bite of the parfaits you so lovingly made, Mizuki!
Mizuki: In that case...! Bon appetite!
